        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 1 at 10:14PM MDT until August 1 at 10:45PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 1013 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 15 miles south of
Dodson, or 20 miles northeast of Zortman, moving north at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Dodson, Phillips, and Wagner.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
